title: A Sneak Peak at Fashion Week
text:
Fall clothes are barely in stores, but the spring 2016 collections hit the runway this week in New York. This season, the cityâ€™s gritty, crowded fashion week is drawing fresh attention from European luxury brands.
On Friday, Givenchy will show in New York instead of its home, Paris, and give away 1,200 tickets to the public, in addition to the fashion editors and store buyers who typically attend shows.
